<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<title>Finite Element Heat Conduction Analysis of a Turbine Blade | Mateng Cheng</title>
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Finite element heat conduction analysis of a turbine blade using MATLAB, Galerkin's method, triangular elements, and ABAQUS validation."
		/>
	</head>

	<body>
		<header class="site-header">
			<nav>
				<a href="/" class="logo">Mateng Cheng</a>

				<div class="nav-links">
					<a href="/">Home</a>
					<a href="/#projects">Projects</a>
					<a href="/#contact">Contact</a>
				</div>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main id="top">
			<section class="project-hero">
				<a class="back-link" href="/#projects">← Back to Projects</a>

				<p class="eyebrow">Finite Element Analysis · Heat Conduction · MATLAB / ABAQUS</p>

				<h1>Finite Element Heat Conduction Analysis of a Turbine Blade</h1>

				<p class="hero-text">
					A finite element analysis project solving a two-dimensional heat conduction problem
					in one-eighth of a turbine blade using Galerkin’s method, linear triangular elements,
					MATLAB implementation, and ABAQUS validation.
				</p>

				<div class="project-meta">
					<div>
						<span>Tools</span>
						<p>MATLAB, ABAQUS</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<span>Methods</span>
						<p>Galerkin Method, FEM, Heat Transfer</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<span>Institution</span>
						<p>Columbia University</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section">
				<div class="hero-image-grid">
					<figure class="hero-figure">
						<img
							src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/fine-temperature-contour-custom.png"
							alt="Fine mesh temperature contour for turbine blade heat conduction"
						/>
						<figcaption>Temperature contour from the fine-mesh MATLAB FEM model.</figcaption>
					</figure>

					<figure class="hero-figure">
						<img
							src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/abaqus-fine-temperature-contour-custom.png"
							alt="ABAQUS fine mesh temperature contour for turbine blade"
						/>
						<figcaption>ABAQUS fine-mesh temperature contour used for validation.</figcaption>
					</figure>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section two-column">
				<div>
					<h2>Project Overview</h2>
				</div>

				<div>
					<p>
						This project analyzed heat conduction in a turbine blade section by taking advantage
						of symmetry and modeling one-eighth of the blade. The work derived the strong form,
						weak form, and finite element discretization of the heat conduction problem, then
						implemented the numerical solver in MATLAB using linear triangular elements.
					</p>

					<p>
						The MATLAB results were compared against ABAQUS simulations under coarse and fine
						meshes. The comparison included temperature contours, normal heat flux, flux vector
						fields, and boundary-condition validation. The results show that the MATLAB
						implementation agrees well with ABAQUS, supporting the accuracy and feasibility of
						the Galerkin FEM solver.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section">
				<div class="stats-grid">
					<div class="stat-card">
						<span>Coarse Mesh</span>
						<strong>267 nodes</strong>
						<p>Coarse triangular mesh with 455 elements generated from ABAQUS.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="stat-card">
						<span>Fine Mesh</span>
						<strong>1958 nodes</strong>
						<p>Fine triangular mesh with 2287 elements for convergence comparison.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="stat-card">
						<span>Element Type</span>
						<strong>Linear Triangles</strong>
						<p>Used three-node triangular elements with linear shape functions.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="stat-card">
						<span>Validation</span>
						<strong>MATLAB vs. ABAQUS</strong>
						<p>Compared temperature and normal flux results across meshes.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section two-column">
				<div>
					<h2>My Role</h2>
				</div>

				<div>
					<ul class="role-list">
						<li>Derived the strong and weak forms for the heat conduction problem.</li>
						<li>Implemented Galerkin finite element formulation using linear triangular elements.</li>
						<li>Assembled the global stiffness matrix and force vector in MATLAB.</li>
						<li>Computed temperature fields and heat flux vector fields for coarse and fine meshes.</li>
						<li>Compared MATLAB numerical results with ABAQUS FEM simulations.</li>
						<li>
							Analyzed mesh refinement, boundary-condition accuracy, and flux singularities near
							sharp geometry points.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section two-column">
				<div>
					<h2>Mesh Design</h2>
				</div>

				<div>
					<p>
						The turbine blade geometry was discretized using linear triangular elements.
						Both coarse and fine meshes were used to study convergence behavior and compare
						the sensitivity of temperature and flux fields to mesh density.
					</p>

					<div class="inline-gallery">
						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/coarse-mesh-custom.png"
								alt="Coarse triangular mesh for turbine blade"
							/>
							<figcaption>Coarse mesh with boundary nodes and triangular elements.</figcaption>
						</figure>

						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/fine-mesh-custom.png"
								alt="Fine triangular mesh for turbine blade"
							/>
							<figcaption>Fine mesh used for convergence and validation.</figcaption>
						</figure>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section two-column">
				<div>
					<h2>Temperature & Flux Results</h2>
				</div>

				<div>
					<p>
						The temperature contours from coarse and fine meshes show similar thermal patterns,
						indicating convergence of the numerical solution. The normal flux results match the
						boundary condition trend well overall, while sharp geometry points create local
						singular behavior.
					</p>

					<div class="inline-gallery">
						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/coarse-temperature-contour-custom.png"
								alt="Temperature contour using coarse mesh"
							/>
							<figcaption>Temperature contour using the coarse mesh.</figcaption>
						</figure>

						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/normal-flux-comparison-custom.png"
								alt="Normal flux comparison between calculated and boundary flux"
							/>
							<figcaption>Normal flux comparison for coarse and fine meshes.</figcaption>
						</figure>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section two-column">
				<div>
					<h2>MATLAB / ABAQUS Validation</h2>
				</div>

				<div>
					<p>
						To verify the MATLAB implementation, the same heat conduction problem was solved in
						ABAQUS. The temperature and heat flux contours from ABAQUS were compared with the
						custom MATLAB FEM results under both coarse and fine mesh settings.
					</p>

					<div class="inline-gallery">
						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/coarse-temperature-validation-custom.png"
								alt="Coarse mesh temperature validation between MATLAB and ABAQUS"
							/>
							<figcaption>Coarse mesh temperature validation between MATLAB and ABAQUS.</figcaption>
						</figure>

						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/coarse-normal-flux-validation-custom.png"
								alt="Coarse mesh normal flux validation between MATLAB and ABAQUS"
							/>
							<figcaption>Coarse mesh normal flux validation between MATLAB and ABAQUS.</figcaption>
						</figure>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section two-column">
				<div>
					<h2>Fine Mesh Validation</h2>
				</div>

				<div>
					<p>
						Fine mesh validation was used to further compare the MATLAB Galerkin FEM solver
						against ABAQUS. The fine mesh results provide a clearer view of convergence and
						improve the spatial resolution of both temperature and heat flux fields.
					</p>

					<div class="inline-gallery">
						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/fine-temperature-validation-custom.png"
								alt="Fine mesh temperature validation between MATLAB and ABAQUS"
							/>
							<figcaption>Fine mesh temperature validation between MATLAB and ABAQUS.</figcaption>
						</figure>

						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/fine-normal-flux-validation-custom.png"
								alt="Fine mesh normal flux validation between MATLAB and ABAQUS"
							/>
							<figcaption>Fine mesh normal flux validation between MATLAB and ABAQUS.</figcaption>
						</figure>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section two-column">
				<div>
					<h2>Algorithm Design</h2>
				</div>

				<div>
					<p>
						The MATLAB solver was organized into pre-processing, analysis, and post-processing
						steps. The workflow included loading mesh connectivity and node locations,
						computing local stiffness matrices and force vectors, applying boundary conditions,
						assembling the global system, and solving for temperature and flux fields.
					</p>

					<div class="inline-gallery">
						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/bandwidth-diagrams-custom.png"
								alt="Bandwidth diagrams for global stiffness matrix"
							/>
							<figcaption>Bandwidth diagrams showing sparsity behavior of the stiffness matrix.</figcaption>
						</figure>

						<figure>
							<img
								src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/coarse-flux-field-custom.png"
								alt="Flux field diagram with coarse mesh"
							/>
							<figcaption>Flux vector field computed on the coarse mesh.</figcaption>
						</figure>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="section">
				<div class="section-title">
					<h2>Project Gallery</h2>
					<p>Mesh diagrams, temperature contours, flux fields, and MATLAB / ABAQUS validation results.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="gallery-grid">
					<figure>
						<img
							src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/temperature-results-comparison-custom.png"
							alt="Temperature results comparison between coarse and fine meshes"
						/>
						<figcaption>Temperature comparison between coarse and fine mesh solutions.</figcaption>
					</figure>

					<figure>
						<img
							src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/fine-flux-field-custom.png"
							alt="Flux field diagram with fine mesh"
						/>
						<figcaption>Flux vector field computed on the fine mesh.</figcaption>
					</figure>

					<figure>
						<img
							src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/abaqus-coarse-temperature-contour-custom.png"
							alt="ABAQUS coarse mesh temperature contour"
						/>
						<figcaption>ABAQUS coarse mesh temperature contour.</figcaption>
					</figure>

					<figure>
						<img
							src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/abaqus-coarse-flux-contour-custom.png"
							alt="ABAQUS coarse mesh flux contour"
						/>
						<figcaption>ABAQUS coarse mesh heat flux contour.</figcaption>
					</figure>

					<figure>
						<img
							src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/abaqus-fine-temperature-contour-custom.png"
							alt="ABAQUS fine mesh temperature contour"
						/>
						<figcaption>ABAQUS fine mesh temperature contour.</figcaption>
					</figure>

					<figure>
						<img
							src="/projects/heat-conduction-turbine-blade/abaqus-fine-flux-contour-custom.png"
							alt="ABAQUS fine mesh flux contour"
						/>
						<figcaption>ABAQUS fine mesh heat flux contour.</figcaption>
					</figure>
				</div>
			</section>

			
		</main>

		<a class="back-to-top" href="#top" aria-label="Back to top">↑</a>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
